Convicted killer Oscar Pistorius is heading to court over his delayed parole. Legal expert, Benedict Phiri spoke with eNCA's Tumelo Mothotoane about the case. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Convicted killer Oscar Pistorius is eligible for parole. But whether he is granted it is still to be decided. WATCH | The pace of Oscar Pistorius' parole process The Paralympian feels the process is taking too long and is heading to court. Legal expert Benedict Phiri says his parole is now in the hands of the case management committee.